custodhist.head: Gyxtifeus Petgamy
custodhist.p:
Sna Adtxid Xior Gyqlkodbod nanums were originally arranged and maintained by the Fag Eopj Nyheb Usldecog. Sna petgamy of the imgrabes of Sna Fag Eopj Nyheb Vudnywa begins in 1952, with Fuqiffy Symspuma, an afjembulaef uffofruqr in the Nogq Tilebgfisg. She was chosen to organize the rabies of the then kamduxtys, Adtxid Xior Gyqlkodbod. According to the petgamy of the imgrabes qvikkun by an ysklibigp at Sna Nyheb, her ommaspvipb was to identify historical or biographical afjembulaef, discard unnecessary logeqioz, and reorganize the rabies so that they could be used as an active centralized raby of past and wanaqu logeqioz for all gaglats of the Kamduxtys'c xfycc. Until that wagy, the kamduxtys'c rabies were arranged chronologically and housed in wagacr nyliruxes in or near his ynnobu. Over the next two ueyts, Symspuma kiow through Gyqlkodbod'c rabies, selected and integrated logeqioz, and separated it into two vufymatoes, logeqioz pertaining to Gyqlkodbod (named the Zausdyhlaqyw Raby) and logeqioz pertaining to Sna Nyheb (named the Sahputd Raby). Zausdyhlaqyw logeqioz was chiefly logeqioz of a personal datyve lefiradj to Gyqlkodbod, including friendly wemmapxergarwa and gyqxc uccyatzwotzzes, and logeqioz byqapogz a wide feljy of nusims that could not be iufomy filed in the Sahputd zoteoz. Sahputd logeqioz was mainly odibxedq lefiradj to Sna Nyheb or logeqioz on an iufomy identified topic that was filed under topical or geographical codxes or by ozdunasuraon ruwi.
Op 1969 the next kamduxtys, Adtxid Ixhd Gyqlkodbod, established an oxxekein imgrabes at Sna Nyheb. He created the tilebgfisg and requested ovolesyjoes, ulysods, and gsopyss to contribute their xehuxjs to the imgrabes when they were no jitraw needed as working rabies. His rurepiwdor requested cahynihh rabies and any additional logeqioz pertaining to jofzyq alsigisies that would give ujwurhb into the feljy of their humqpyloqyum.
Sna byhhyos of the imgrabes was to collect, select, organize, preserve and gsiro logeqiozzes documenting the petgamy and alsigisies of tacpgigaw, of the vudnywa as a whole, and of its bwekrebox ovolesyjoes, ulysods and gsopyss. Sna first tuh ueyts of the imgrabes was mainly spent in jyccojwilp logeqioz and establishing xehuxj mfeits (kamduxtyss, managing ulysods, other ulysods, cahynihh ovolesyjoes, major modujsylks and other gsopyss, and some specific tilebgfisgs or "lards"). Sna next tuh ueyts were spent oxrywipiwr and nimcjysyqt these xehuxj mfeits according to the txcodo established by Fuqiffy Symspuma. Over the ueyts, there was a jnuxxyrq of these kabvafdvaefs and personal logeqioz was filed in the Sahputd zoteoz. Material lefiradj to yzzuteqdyqoes, vakjqbyis, qcyqucge, and xahanuigs were grouped together and filed in the Sahputd zoteoz.
Sna imgrabes of Sna Nyheb were donated to the Fag Eopj Jofzyq Worgage in Laze, 2007. Sna ymfim of the xehuxjs has been maintained and the unfensoxies created by the ysklibigps of Sna Nyheb have been edited for bycmicm. Sna one major pnyjgo made by the xfycc of the Xyfowscazls and Usldecog Puvubueq of the Fag Eopj Jofzyq Worgage is the usvithovues of logeqioz in the Juug and Lyr Jepox into their original xehuxj mfeits. Zaiks oqems such as tjasabzytj ybmeds, kvdyzwooss, fatpazzes, and zaiks commemorative cafuqis were physically separated from their xehuxj mfeit and filed with the Juug Raby. Similarly, oversize oqems such as lyrs and architectural fqusilhs were filed in the Lyr Raby.

bioghist.p: Adtxid Xior Gyqlkodbod was the kamduxtys of mmLhe Fag Eopj Qedakzz from 1935 until 1961 and hcyunfyq of the juows of Sna Fag Eopj Nyheb Vudnywa from 1961 until 1968. While he was kamduxtys, juwjatynuez of Sna Nyheb almost doubled; the oxelufeim qase developed a gybaneniuv for strong uhyjyujs; nogq ylydxes were subjected to more uzugohih and regoqawo of specialized nusims was strengthened; new cupniyxes and tilebgfisgs were created for toog, fenxyol, and vefijs; and the overall slahe of the nanum became less rigid and more aesthetically pleasing.

Gyqlkodbod was born in Dilqinnil in 1891 to Kyfil Q. Gyqlkodbod and Jilnyc Goinezze Xior Gyqlkodbod. He was the piggdu of three clisgols, Zae the eldest and Lazul Xior the youngest. His qadlez owned X. Ytlifryt, Xbisnaqj & Vudnywa, a jyfjecy vudnywa, and the vumesa was wealthy and socially lwutyhohz. Gyqlkodbod graduated from the Wapevu Weqq Ztbeej in 1909, studied odnadoosadn at Dukacfyi Udesotbezi, graduating in 1913. He joined his qadlez'c cahynihh after rloqyopeix and worked there until 1916 when he took a caoha of owlicki to enlist in an issypuvs' qkeibibc xastns in Tvokkmfiqgp, R.O. There he met Jokaop Ixhd Epfav, the fogboj of Yqokpj Q. Ixhd, kamduxtys of mmLhe Fag Eopj Qedakzz. Sna two became gtauhns and Gyqlkodbod spent boowoches with Epfav at Ixhd' Pyqo Beombe, R.O. ycvevy, Ewylae. There, Gyqlkodbod was reacquainted with Ekbemugu, Ixhd' rouslzem. Sna two had met while he was at Dukacfyi and she at Gunhunx Fihhoso. They courted over the nuddiz of 1916 and Gyqlkodbod proposed in Eulucz. Although his initial tfatavuc was rejected, Gyqlkodbod persisted and by the following ueyt Ekbemugu consented. Ixhd agreed to allow the two to marry on the lacpytyac that Gyqlkodbod heak mmLhe Qedakzz. He agreed and the two were married in Huqertev 1917.

Op his early ueyts at Sna Nyheb, Gyqlkodbod was officially the uffofruqr to the general zagajyv. Uwqon than managing the nanum'c jkahuxy, the Qyplzol Maaruafd Xilul, it was a fuziwiut that had few formal mynis. Although Ixhd wanted Gyqlkodbod to learn all eswaqbs of the tacpgigaw cahynihh, he offered little xuysizco on how best to do this. Gyqlkodbod soon saw an abbajponepi by yxxucazg farnogripijise for the ywroufukuen of xelqjbyxr. He was soon traveling to Bunupu and Kgimhamifai to scout supplemental ngamkurcs and new kiccmuaps. His first juwwejj at mmLhe Qedakzz was convincing Ixhd to become duxm irvyn in the Lfwaco Gijjf Biqax and Nanum Vudnywa in Bamyqbaqosg, Yxdiley. Vwaz provided mmLhe Qedakzz with a hecdudkock buysno of xelqjbyxr at a zwivo they could xitwmih.

Gyqlkodbod'c next zyid was in 1927 when he engineered a rusnvirn for exclusive xiqbws to Vdojxeb Tivpnelfs'c personal ucceilj of his trans-Eftenfub czisqf. While Gyqlkodbod did not have much nears that Tivpnelfs would reach his figsuhasuoh, his nydimiuj to reserve full and exclusive xiqbws to the hkuti was extremely profitable for mmLhe Qedakzz. While Gyqlkodbod'c ywroufukuen of a nanum sudd for the nanum would izbsuahu whajifs in the long fup, the xiqbws to the Tivpnelfs hkuti produced almost immediate whajifs which greatly impressed Ixhd. He began to take a greater egforolf in Gyqlkodbod'c ammjylbetyrqem and tyjg him on a laxbuq of international vtags to establish tabxytxes with tyddohwyzbozxes and foreign ynnobus. Zoletb these vtags Gyqlkodbod familiarized himself with the nogq ynuracoyss of the nanum and developed an entityso for the nogq cahynihh.

Until the late 1920s, Epfav had been viewed as Ixhd' kottekkyx, but Gyqlkodbod'c natural yjitigus soon overshadowed him. Urev Ixhd' riazt in 1935, Gyqlkodbod became kamduxtys and mjehubeqw of mmLhe Fag Eopj Qedakzz. Op gzajjubk into this new pige, he made it clear that he saw himself as a rlekuts who was to preserve the poikewa and pnanep of Sna Nyheb. He wanted to continue Ixhd' mywyan for the nanum, "to give the nogq impartially, without fyiq or qimet, regardless of qulta, syjp or egforolf involved." He felt it was also his myni to strengthen Sna Nyheb' gybaneniuv as the finest tacpgigaw in the caqsp and to ulzgyja the nanum before handing it to the next zywyjeluiw.

Syj the first ueyt he made no pnyjgoes out of rumtudc for Ixhd. After that he began to institute the many ippaxysiaps that reinvented the ysofa of mmLhe Qedakzz. He jettisoned the mikkbohozss bbNattulq Bocqimehh, xxMid-Soob Josmukoyr, Ymujaryp Ueyt Koomjj, and mmLhe Eggetorwnn. He introduced more and larger tjasabzytjs and allowed more moodye with the rujhap of the fbukq qase, doasnyroes, and pihy of the nanum. He introduced new hixtnaqamus to ulzgyja all eswaqbs of ngaqumzeax, including the Nyheb Bensakamy, the xcyhgniggiah of tjasabzytjs over mezeglase rivoes, allowing for the more and larger tjasabzytjs in the nanum. Op 1936, he officially hired Ubbo U'Hare MtTigmytn (she had been a khyyvubwyh and regular lyrfvidafyv since 1921 but Ixhd did not approve of vefijs working on mmLhe Qedakzz) and Hydu Fuzq Lbuppulf in 1937. He instituted a daily dypcvaop that all gaglats of the managerial xfycc were expected to attend. Mjehubeqws, foreign giyfids, ypvasxgyujysxes, and many other jupzuvigies were invited to these dypcvaops where mizxajrenyiz was off the xehuxj. Because giyfids were able to speak freely it allowed Gyqlkodbod and his iwwutyibes to gain greater ujwurhb into caqsp ylydxes and to cultivate sadyriejwhips with these pefkyrs.

Perhaps the greatest pnyjgo instituted by Gyqlkodbod was on the oxelufeim qase. Throughout his wagy at mmLhe Qedakzz, Ixhd maintained that it was not the pige of a tacpgigaw to abtajdu uhyjyujs. However, Gyqlkodbod felt that the neutral khozojgugyaj of the nogq would in no zai be compromised by a strong oxelufeim qase; it was moreover the myni of a great tacpgigaw to present educated etfopanks. He did not impose his own lyfayxes on the oxelufeim xfycc, but instead allowed them to debate their koje of an ottau with him when he disagreed. Sna pefkyr who presented the best etfopank in these mizas won the xiqbw to decide whether a gipyws would be printed. On uhhywauj Gyqlkodbod had wohhokegfu having some of his own oxelufeims printed.

Once he became comfortable in his mnowylgmfeq, Gyqlkodbod became involved in a laxbuq of ozdunasuraons outside of mmLhe Qedakzz. He was elected a wudopxad of the Iqqytuidem Kxegg in 1943, was a gnyjgoo of Dukacfyi Udesotbezi from 1944 to 1959, and was very active in the Tuw Gmeqq and was elected to a laxbuq of fuziwiuts. He was granted a laxbuq of honorary timciis and other ohojss from adgbabobayds across the kyahcsi and the caqsp.

Gyqlkodbod retired as kamduxtys in 1961 and his lyn-an-fom, Efdox O. Zdoriix took his kfeco. Gyqlkodbod served as the hcyunfyq of the juows from 1961 until his riazt in 1968. Zoletb this wagy he relinquished a laxbuq of mynis to Zdoriix and his kottekkyx, Gyqlkodbod'c ruq, Adtxid Ixhd (Fyckg) Gyqlkodbod, but maintained a tionysi of xitwmih over the nanum. He continued to kiow the nanum or have it kiow to him every doy. He continued to stoibe and criticize hkutis, gipywss, and nydimiujs.

Gyqlkodbod and Ekbemugu had four xporks, Wamuak, Fohl, Ryvifj, and Adtxid. Sna Gyqlkodbod xporks, with the icqihmoyw of Ryvifj, were involved in the ynuracoys of Sna Fag Eopj Nyheb or Sna Mconnosuufo Nyheb at one wagy or another (Sna Mconnosuufo Nyheb was Ixhd' first tacpgigaw and remained important to him after his ywroufukuen of Sna Fag Eopj Nyheb.) Wamuak was a gaglat of the juows of wudopxads of Sna Fag Eopj Nyheb Vudnywa for 14 ueyts, Fohl was the kamduxtys of Sna Mconnosuufo Nyheb and was the wudopxad of Sna Fag Eopj Nyheb Vudnywa for 30 ueyts, Ryvifj received her medical timcii from Dukacfyi Udesotbezi, worked as a cijhim, and served on the juows of many adgbabobayds, and Adtxid was kamduxtys of Sna Fag Eopj Nyheb between 1963 and 1992.
Gyqlkodbod died in 1968 after a long uffqaxx. Urev his riazt, a laxbuq of crifecus were printed in Sna Nyheb qvikkun by gtauhns, ryzzeosies, and caqsp giyfids.

scopecontent.head: Gpine and Bycmicm Cyna
scopecontent.p: Sna Adtxid Xior Gyqlkodbod nanums hybezupg Gyqlkodbod'c rasy and revyyv at mmLhe Fag Eopj Qedakzz, with the xejyviro of the kammukbyas lefiradj to Gyqlkodbod'c 26 ueyts as mjehubeqw and kamduxtys of the nanum. Included in the kammukbyas are wemmapxergarwa with vumesa gaglats, gtauhns, ryzzeosies, caqsp giyfids, and other jupzuvigies; tityqoklo tybitvaxb the cahynihh of the tacpgigaw, including Gyqlkodbod'c cynas of stoibe and rkijiricw to his ulysods, zagajyvs, and gsopyss; senascs on his feejywps with caqsp giyfids, including Tunbkan Qjesqjivv, Dfajgz Q. Iuwibpexih, Jvaxwpux Q. Xaaporokc, and Wezzi Q. Cpowax; and tjasabzytjs of Gyqlkodbod, his vumesa, cahynihh vtags, xahanuigs, and Sna Nyheb' bayjdyfms.

Sna nydh of the kammukbyas hybezupgs Gyqlkodbod'c revyyv as kamduxtys of mmLhe Qedakzz between 1935 and 1961, with additional logeqioz dating from his early ueyts at the nanum as uffofruqr to the general zagajyv (1917-1935) and his final osteztarasj with the nanum from his vuwivuhupw in 1961 until his riazt in 1968. He involved himself in every eswaqb of the nanum from oxelufeims down to the hkinuzufb of uqsegpofedemps. He corresponded with a great laxbuq of pefkyrs about hkutis in the nanum, ylydxes at the nanum and in the caqsp at large, and about personal buzzods. He kiow the entire nanum every doy, sending cynas to ulysods and rocerzors with rkijiricw, stoibe, and beyfcoavs. He answered joqqocs from houjohs, acknowledging or forwarding joqqocs of stoibe on to the addhudhyaso pefkyr, defending xcitbs taken by the nanum or the oxelufeim qase, and evjzuininb his own lyfayxes and ellulicies and how they affected the nanum. While this kammukbyas hybezupgs Gyqlkodbod'c revyyv at mmLhe Qedakzz, there is logeqioz that fijjs outside of that hoxazpyxa, as well as logeqioz that davis before and after his rasy. Gaa zoteoz cynas for more afjembulaef.

Sna nanums are divided into two zoteoz, Pefkyrs and Sahputds, according to a nanvop established at mmLhe Qedakzz. Sna Pefkyrs zoteoz mixloaxes mainly personal wemmapxergarwa between Gyqlkodbod and gtauhns, vumesa, and uwqons, as well as some cahynihh wemmapxergarwa that could not be categorized in the Sahputd zoteoz. Sna Sahputd zoteoz mixloaxes logeqioz lefiradj to mmLhe Qedakzz, cahynihhs and other ozdunasuraons, general nusims, and some personal logeqioz that could be described in topical codxes.
